      "created_at": "2025-02-03T15:56:14.504Z",
      "cooked": "<p>My power output on an Elite Direto (original version, updated to the latest firmware) with a Zwift Cog (single speed) is essentially flat during TrainerDay sessions.</p>\n<p>I assume TD is supposed to vary the resistance throughout the workout until my power output matches the target. Regardless of rpm, I stay at approximately the same power, which is well above the workout target. This is consistent over 60 minute workouts.</p>\n<p>I assume this means the Direto isn\u2019t in ERG mode. I don\u2019t have much experience using a trainer, so it\u2019s possible I\u2019m overlooking some obvious solution on the trainer itself or within the Elite or TrainerDay software. But I\u2019ve poked around and don\u2019t see any obvious fix.</p>\n<p>How can I get TR working so that the difficulty automatically adjusts with the workout?</p>",
